    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-08T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-08T11:00:00-05:00" n="155"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d155">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112/9729</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-08T17:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 8, 1918, 5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 5.20 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>921. War Trade Board [from <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1"
                        >Sheldon</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 1182. Our 1068, July 22.<note n="1" xml:id="d155fn1">Not printed.</note> The
                    inter-Allied committee for the correlation of the published black lists has now
                    been designated as <pb facs="0201" n="1035" xml:id="pg_1035"/> the conference to
                    consider those applications for licenses to trade with the enemy which are to be
                    referred to London conference now in operation. Some slight changes in classes
                    of cases to be referred here may be suggested after next meeting. Meetings held
                    every two weeks, but cases can be handled most expeditiously if referred here as
                    they arise rather than waiting to send them in anticipation of a particular
                    meeting.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
